 This area lies to the west of{Bury}   
 and north of{Radcliffe.}It contains a 
 mixture of industrial, residential and
 farming areas as well as some land    
 that is basically wild.It is bisected 
 diagonally{S.W.to N.E.}by the{        
{Manchester Victoria}to Bury railway{  
{line.}In the north-west corner lies { 
{Ainsworth}village.{Elton reservoir}   
 covers about a third of a square      
 kilometre.The A58 Bury to {Bolton}road
 runs parallel to the railway across   
 the area.The landscape is a pleasant  
 variety of beautiful hills punctuated 
 by tall chimneys and occasional       
 industrial scars.{Peel's Monument}    
 above Holcombe is a prominent feature 
 and although not in the area it is    
 visible from virtually anywhere inside
 it.
